On Escalation Ticket # 00412909 the new comment has been added: After asking the customer to test this with both apps turned off the customer returned with this.
The issue with the Endpoint Protector service does not occur at regular intervals. it happens occasionally without a predictable pattern.
The problematic endpoints have been functioning without issues for the past 30 days, and tampering mode is working as expected, even with both the CrowdStrike and Versa agents installed.
This problem has only affected a few endpoints. All other endpoints in the environment, which also have the CrowdStrike and Versa agents installed, have not experienced any issues.
Given this, it appears that uninstalling the Versa and CrowdStrike agents may not be necessary for the investigation, as the problem does not consistently replicate across all endpoints with these agents installed.
